% Leinster: Foundational work on diversity measurement
% - Proves diversity cannot be captured by single number; requires a profile
% - Hill numbers parameterized by q: emphasis on rare (q→0) vs common (q→∞) species
% - When diversity profiles cross, ordering is ambiguous
% - Generalizes Shannon entropy to similarity-sensitive diversity measures
% - Key insight: different q values answer different questions about diversity
